<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - ELECTRICAL TROUBLESHOOTING FANS -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Engine Cooling Fan Controls, Horton And Kysor With Cummins ISM And AHD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Engine Cooling Fan Controls, Horton And Kysor With Cummins ISM And AHD</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0819605">
            <title>Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON and KYSOR ENGINE WITH AHD and ISM ENGINE circuit diagram in CTS-5298 or S08225.</para>
            <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires, etc.
            </para>
            <table id="t0819608" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.72in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.46in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (227) from the solenoid pigtail. Measure resistance from
                                    (227) terminal B to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(227), terminal B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23-GA or 11-GU between connector (227)
                                    and ground, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (251). Measure resistance from (251) terminal C to (227)
                                    terminal A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(251), term. C to (2274) term. A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23A between connector (227) and (251),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance from (251) terminal C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(251), terminal C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 23D, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect (227) to solenoid. Install a jumper from (251) terminal C to 12 volts.
                                    Does the solenoid energize?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>Solenoid energizes.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace fan solenoid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect connectors. The fan control circuits and components check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch (228) and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON and KYSOR ENGINE WITH AHD and ISM ENGINE circuit diagram in CTS-5298 or S08225.</para>
            <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires, etc.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform preceding test,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="x0819605">Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</hotlnk>, before performing this
                        test.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0819609" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch (228) and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.64in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connectors (251), (252) and (190). At A/C pressure switch, measure
                                    resistance across the switch terminals. (If you suspect the switch is not opening at
                                    300 PSI, replace switch.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A/C pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance from (251) terminal T to (228) terminal A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(251) terminal T to (228) terminal A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 23C between (251) and (228), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance from (251) terminal T to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(251), terminal T to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuits 23C, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance from (252) terminal 10 to (228) terminal B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(252) terminal 10 to (228) terminal B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 23-GB or 97-G between (252) and (228), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance from (190) terminal V to (228) terminal B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(190) terminal V to (228) terminal B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 23-GB or 97-GA between (252) and (190). Repair condition.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnct connectors. The A/C pressure switch circuits and components check good.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing (Optional) Engine Fan Override Switch (659)</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON and KYSOR ENGINE FAN WITH AHD and ISM ENGINE circuit diagram in CTS-5298 or S08225.
            </para>
            <para>This switch is intended to last the life of the truck. If it is determined to be defective it should
                be replaced. It is not a repairable item.
            </para>
            <table id="t0819610" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing (Optional) Engine Fan Override Switch (659)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.64in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="1.10in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.39in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connectors (659). With the switch in the "Off" position, measure the
                                    resistance between terminals 4 and 5.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Fan Override Switch (659), terminals 4 and 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With the switch in the "On" position, measure the resistance between terminals 5
                                    and 6.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine Fan Override Switch (659), terminals 5 and 6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect 12 volts to terminal 7 and ground to terminal 8. Does the LED
                                    illuminate?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>LED illuminates.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect 12 volts to terminal 7 and ground to terminal 8. Does the LED
                                    illuminate?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>LED illuminates.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect 12 volts to terminal 6 and ground to terminal 1. Does the LED
                                    illuminate?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>LED illuminates.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Switch tests good. Reconnect switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>Switch operates correctly.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Identify problems with circuit 62M to panel feed adapter or circuits 11-GR or
                                    23-GY to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
